WEBVTT

00:00:15.870 --> 00:00:18.620
Jojo's Bizarre Adventure

00:00:15.990 --> 00:00:18.490
Diamond is Unbreakable

00:01:17.070 --> 00:01:21.960
Episode 3  The Nijimura Brothers, Part 1

00:01:19.050 --> 00:01:22.190
Yeah. The issue with Angelo's been resolved.

00:01:23.620 --> 00:01:25.770
But I won't be coming back for a while.

00:01:26.460 --> 00:01:28.870
That other photo we've been investigating...

00:01:29.300 --> 00:01:31.460
Send it over, too.

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:37.450
Yeah, the one that the Speedwagon 
Foundation found in Egypt ten years ago.

00:01:37.450 --> 00:01:39.820
I think I might finally know what it means.

00:01:40.490 --> 00:01:41.520
Please.

00:01:43.480 --> 00:01:46.460
Yeah, thanks to him.

00:01:47.710 --> 00:01:54.420
Josuke! I killed your grandpa,
but you have no right to kill me!

00:01:54.840 --> 00:02:00.590
If you kill me, you'll end up 
a cursed soul, just like me!

00:02:03.410 --> 00:02:07.100
Don't go telling people what 
they can and can't do.

00:02:08.250 --> 00:02:12.110
M-M-My right hand! My hand!

00:02:12.110 --> 00:02:15.040
No one's going to execute you.

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:17.360
Not me, and not Jotaro, either.

00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:20.410
You're not going to be executed,

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:22.530
and you're not going back to jail.

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:24.770
Josuke, I'll leave the rest to you.

00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:28.370
Wh-What do you plan to do 
with me, you bastards?!

00:02:28.590 --> 00:02:31.100
Repent for eternity, Angelo!

00:02:31.100 --> 00:02:35.080
For all of those you killed, 
including my Gramps!

00:02:44.750 --> 00:02:46.560
Damn it...

00:02:47.130 --> 00:02:49.810
Don't you dare get cocky!

00:02:49.810 --> 00:02:55.070
I'm sure he'll kill you both for me.

00:02:55.070 --> 00:02:56.780
What? "He"?

00:02:57.150 --> 00:03:00.140
That's right. The one wearing a school uniform,

00:03:00.140 --> 00:03:02.610
who gave me this power.

00:03:03.050 --> 00:03:04.040
What?

00:03:04.390 --> 00:03:05.240
It can't be...

00:03:05.730 --> 00:03:09.050
Are you saying someone can
willingly give another a Stand?

00:03:09.050 --> 00:03:10.180
Are you scared?

00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:14.290
Huh? How is that supposed to scare us?

00:03:14.290 --> 00:03:18.090
No... Angelo's not a Stand user by birth.

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:22.340
It was a mystery how he 
obtained his Stand powers.

00:03:22.680 --> 00:03:26.850
But if there is actually a person 
who can give others Stands...

00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:28.850
Terrifying, isn't it?

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:31.600
Want me to tell you?

00:03:34.620 --> 00:03:39.520
It was last year, so 1998,

00:03:39.900 --> 00:03:43.860
on a night about a month 
before my execution.

00:03:45.160 --> 00:03:48.820
I couldn't sleep that night...

00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:52.870
I was just staring blankly 
up at the ceiling of my cell.

00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:56.960
It was a completely silent night.

00:03:56.960 --> 00:03:58.750
But then...

00:04:01.490 --> 00:04:05.370
I should've been the only one in that dark cell,

00:04:05.370 --> 00:04:07.010
but he was there.

00:04:07.980 --> 00:04:10.810
The guy in the school uniform.

00:04:11.420 --> 00:04:13.560
H-Hey! How long have you been there?!

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:14.810
Where'd you come from?!

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:19.070
Wha...

00:04:19.380 --> 00:04:22.410
It was a very old bow and arrow.

00:04:22.410 --> 00:04:26.070
It looked like it was centuries old.

00:04:26.070 --> 00:04:28.090
Wh-What are you doing?

00:04:28.090 --> 00:04:32.000
I was so scared, I could almost 
feel my balls shriveling up.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:34.870
But before I even had a chance to scream...

00:05:00.310 --> 00:05:03.070
You're alive. Congratulations.

00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:08.070
That means you've got the aptitude. 
If you didn't, you'd be dead.

00:05:09.400 --> 00:05:13.380
You've just obtained a talent.

00:05:13.890 --> 00:05:18.830
No... It's more accurate to say 
it was pulled from your mind.

00:05:19.130 --> 00:05:22.250
The worse the villain, the more they have...

00:05:22.250 --> 00:05:27.460
This talent that the man 
named DIO called a "Stand."

00:05:31.810 --> 00:05:32.810
DIO?

00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:34.070
Did you say DIO?

00:05:34.730 --> 00:05:36.470
Jotaro? Is something...

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:40.210
What?!

00:05:40.210 --> 00:05:41.840
You fools!

00:05:41.840 --> 00:05:43.610
It looks like you were so busy

00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:46.390
listening to my story that you 
forgot about my Aqua Necklace!

00:05:46.390 --> 00:05:47.450
Angelo, you bastard!

00:05:47.450 --> 00:05:51.270
Josuke! Hurry up and get me out of this rock!

00:05:53.900 --> 00:05:55.790
It would appear that...

00:05:56.220 --> 00:05:59.790
I didn't have enough rage in my heart for you.

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:03.890
What are you doing? Stop messing 
with your stupid hair!

00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:08.090
I'm gonna kill this brat! 
Let me out right now!

00:06:10.190 --> 00:06:11.680
What did you say...

00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:13.220
Don't be rash, Josuke!

00:06:13.530 --> 00:06:15.470
...about my hair?

00:06:15.470 --> 00:06:17.940
Y-You know... If you kill me,

00:06:17.940 --> 00:06:20.370
the guy in the school uniform won't let it slide!

00:06:20.370 --> 00:06:22.650
He lives in this town, too!

00:06:22.650 --> 00:06:25.530
What? Josuke, wait!

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:29.770
Ker-Blam

00:06:42.630 --> 00:06:45.570
Yeah... I just didn't have enough rage earlier.

00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:51.600
I needed to do a great job of burying
that asshole into the rock, like this.

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:56.430
Good grief.

00:06:56.430 --> 00:06:59.580
I wanted to get a bit more out of him.

00:06:59.580 --> 00:07:02.690
Huh? You actually believe 
the crap he was saying?

00:07:02.690 --> 00:07:06.820
It wasn't crap. He said DIO's name.

00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:09.150
Who is that, anyway?

00:07:09.500 --> 00:07:14.230
He's a man that the Joestar family has 
been fighting for over a hundred years.

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:18.290
My friends and I fought DIO and defeated him.

00:07:19.480 --> 00:07:21.970
But there was one thing 
that I didn't understand.

00:07:22.340 --> 00:07:28.970
Back in 1987, why did the man 
called DIO suddenly acquire a Stand?

00:07:28.970 --> 00:07:31.970
Could the same person 
have made him a Stand user?

00:07:31.970 --> 00:07:36.470
Yeah... The guy in the school 
uniform might be our new enemy.

00:07:36.870 --> 00:07:40.820
Or perhaps it's the bow and arrow he had.

00:07:43.590 --> 00:07:46.100
If that's somewhere in this city...

00:07:46.820 --> 00:07:52.070
Then it's hard to believe that 
Angelo's the only danger here.

00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:55.850
Good grief...

00:07:56.760 --> 00:08:00.020
Morioh Town Report

00:08:00.020 --> 00:08:03.000
Morioh Town Report

00:08:05.470 --> 00:08:07.750
It's just like Jotaro said.

00:08:08.360 --> 00:08:11.920
There's no doubt that the worst thing 
imaginable is hiding in this city.

00:08:11.920 --> 00:08:15.140
An extremely terrible danger 
is coming to this city...

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:17.760
No, it's already begun.

00:08:18.290 --> 00:08:24.190
Since the beginning of this year, 1999,
81 people have disappeared in Morioh.

00:08:21.160 --> 00:08:34.570
Abductions &amp; Kidnapping Cases

00:08:24.730 --> 00:08:27.410
Of that number, 45 of them
were young boys and girls.

00:08:27.410 --> 00:08:29.080
Even if some were runaways,

00:08:28.710 --> 00:08:34.570
Have You Seen This Person?

00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:32.690
that's still seven to eight times greater
than Japan's national average per city.

00:08:32.690 --> 00:08:34.570
That number is extreme.

00:08:34.960 --> 00:08:36.070
Not to mention...

00:08:36.070 --> 00:08:37.600
Ryohei Higashikata Dead 
<font size="18">(Morioh Police Officer)</c>

00:08:38.060 --> 00:08:40.210
Josuke's grandfather...

00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:45.000
Koichi, you're even studying after school?

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:46.290
Let's go home.

00:08:47.510 --> 00:08:49.170
Oh, right.

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:53.450
Thank goodness. Josuke 
seems to be feeling better.

00:09:00.950 --> 00:09:02.430
Yo, Angelo.

00:09:02.430 --> 00:09:05.270
Uh... Huh? Hey, was this rock always here?

00:09:05.580 --> 00:09:08.300
Yeah, but it didn't look like this at first.

00:09:08.300 --> 00:09:09.470
At first?

00:09:11.150 --> 00:09:13.680
Well, whatever. Yo, Angelo...

00:09:16.480 --> 00:09:19.740
By the way, what happened to Jotaro?

00:09:19.740 --> 00:09:23.130
Oh, he said he had something 
he wanted to look into.

00:09:23.130 --> 00:09:24.750
He's staying at the Grand Hotel.

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.870
Does it have to do with this city?

00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:29.400
I'm sure it does.

00:09:29.400 --> 00:09:30.490
I see.

00:09:35.010 --> 00:09:36.780
The danger this city faces...

00:09:47.870 --> 00:09:50.020
Huh? Josuke?

00:09:51.020 --> 00:09:54.850
No one's lived in this house for 
about three or four years, right?

00:09:56.650 --> 00:09:59.950
Yeah. It's so run-down that 
there's no way it'd sell.

00:09:59.950 --> 00:10:02.200
It should be torn down and rebuilt.

00:10:02.200 --> 00:10:06.100
No, someone's living here. 
Maybe someone moved in?

00:10:06.100 --> 00:10:08.330
There was someone in the window just now.

00:10:08.330 --> 00:10:12.340
Huh? Nah, that can't be. 
My house is over there, right?

00:10:12.340 --> 00:10:14.890
I'd know right away if someone moved in.

00:10:14.890 --> 00:10:16.880
Besides, realtors are always checking

00:10:16.880 --> 00:10:19.280
to make sure homeless people don't crash there.

00:10:20.280 --> 00:10:22.810
Now that you mention it, that's true.

00:10:22.810 --> 00:10:28.310
How strange. I wonder if I actually saw a ghost...

00:10:28.310 --> 00:10:31.400
H-Hey, don't say stuff like that.

00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:34.480
Ghosts are scary! And we're 
right in front of my house.

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:46.790
Stop gawking at my house, little brat.

00:10:43.780 --> 00:10:45.490
Billion

00:10:46.240 --> 00:10:47.330
Billion

00:10:47.930 --> 00:10:49.580
Say something!

00:10:49.580 --> 00:10:50.820
Koichi!

00:10:50.820 --> 00:10:53.000
Hey! What the hell do you think you're doing?

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:56.420
What? That's my line.

00:10:56.840 --> 00:10:59.430
You two are in front of my house...

00:11:02.930 --> 00:11:06.930
Morioh Landmark 1
<font size="23">The Angelo Stone
</c><font size="15">How to get there: A minute's 
walk from Morioh 
